{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":34090,"name":"","username":"Elendil","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/e/df788c/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-10-02T10:23:38.400Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI want display HP above object and update texture each frame. I use billboard for that. Are there any another posibilities to display HP bar instead use billboards? Or billboards are the best way?\u003cbr\u003e\nCan I use Sprite in 3D scene instead billboards? With sprite I can use texture directly instead Billboards where are material used.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eProblem with this is, when two or more HP bars are displayed it render only one bar. That means if HP is decreased, hpoints are decrease for all displayed HP bars. I think this is because billboards share same one texture. Or be more precise, material. I think this is problematic: \u003ccode\u003em_material = cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt;(\"Materials/MyEmptyBillboard2.xml\");\u003c/code\u003e but when I use\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003em_material = new Material(ctx); \nm_material-\u0026gt;SetTexture(TextureUnit::TU_DIFFUSE, m_texture);\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eit show billboard with gray color.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is how I display HP bar above my cubes (each cube have own billboard)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\tm_texture = new Texture2D(ctx);\n\tm_texture-\u0026gt;SetFilterMode(Urho3D::TextureFilterMode::FILTER_BILINEAR);\n\tm_texture-\u0026gt;SetNumLevels(1);\n\tm_texture-\u0026gt;SetSize(m_i_width, m_i_height, Urho3D::Graphics::GetRGBAFormat(), Urho3D::TEXTURE_DYNAMIC);\n\tm_texture-\u0026gt;SetData(0, 0, 0, m_i_width, m_i_height, m_idata_converted);\n\n\n\t// billboard\n\tm_node_billboard = m_node-\u0026gt;CreateChild(\"HealthBar\");\n\tm_node_billboard-\u0026gt;SetPosition(Vector3(0, 0.8, 0));\n\tm_bs = m_node_billboard-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;BillboardSet\u0026gt;();\n\tm_bs-\u0026gt;SetNumBillboards(1);\n\n\tm_material = cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Material\u0026gt;(\"Materials/MyEmptyBillboard2.xml\");\n\tm_material-\u0026gt;SetTexture(TextureUnit::TU_DIFFUSE, m_texture);\n\tm_bs-\u0026gt;SetMaterial(m_material);\n\t\n\tm_bs-\u0026gt;SetSorted(true);\n\n\tm_bb = m_bs-\u0026gt;GetBillboard(0);\n\tfloat fx = 0.5;\n\tfloat fy = fx / (m_i_width / m_i_height);\n\tm_bb-\u0026gt;size_ = Vector2(fx, fy);\n\tm_bb-\u0026gt;enabled_ = SHOW_HEALTHBAR;\n\n\tm_bs-\u0026gt;Commit();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eand how I update billboard\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eArmorHealthBar-\u0026gt;Render((double)m_i_width, (double)m_i_height, m_idata);\nConvertRGBA();\nm_texture-\u0026gt;SetData(0, 0, 0, m_i_width, m_i_height, m_idata_converted);\nm_material-\u0026gt;SetTexture(TextureUnit::TU_DIFFUSE, m_texture);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-10-02T10:23:38.400Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":106,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":538.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":5639,"topic_slug":"the-right-way-create-billboard-for-hp-bar-and-problem-with-rendering-how-to","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34091,"name":"Justin Miller","username":"jmiller","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jmiller/{size}/2367_2.png","created_at":"2019-10-02T13:49:18.821Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello / mae govannen,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/miegamicis\"\u003e@Miegamicis\u003c/a\u003e’ \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/new-project-template/4428\"\u003eNew Project Template\u003c/a\u003e has a progress bar (seen later in \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/ArnisLielturks/Urho3D-Project-Template/blob/master/Screenshots\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003escreenshots\u003c/a\u003e) which uses Sprites:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003ca href=\"https://github.com/ArnisLielturks/Urho3D-Project-Template/blob/master/Source/Levels/Loading.cpp\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ehttps://github.com/ArnisLielturks/Urho3D-Project-Template/blob/master/Source/Levels/Loading.cpp\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-10-02T13:49:18.821Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":23.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":5639,"topic_slug":"the-right-way-create-billboard-for-hp-bar-and-problem-with-rendering-how-to","display_username":"Justin Miller","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/ArnisLielturks/Urho3D-Project-Template/blob/master/Screenshots","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":7},{"url":"https://github.com/ArnisLielturks/Urho3D-Project-Template/blob/master/Source/Levels/Loading.cpp","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D-Project-Template/Loading.cpp at master · ArnisLielturks/Urho3D-Project-Template · GitHub","clicks":6},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/new-project-template/4428","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"New project template","clicks":1}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":true,"admin":false,"staff":true,"user_id":21,"hidden":false,"trust_level":3,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34092,"name":"","username":"JTippetts","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/jtippetts/{size}/357_2.png","created_at":"2019-10-02T14:04:40.029Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eIn an \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/JTippetts/DungeonBot3000\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eARPG\u003c/a\u003e I did for a game jam recently, I used regular old UI elements for the lifebars. The lifebar widget comprised 2 BorderImage, one for the gray background and one for the green bar, then a \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/JTippetts/DungeonBot3000/blob/master/src/Components/enemylifebar.cpp\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003ecustom component\u003c/a\u003e attached to the enemy object handles Update, and uses the camera to project the enemy’s location to the screen, adds an offset to put it above the head, and changes the widget’s position to the projected position. Then it queries health and max health to adjust the size of the green BorderImage. It worked pretty well:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/loWMzsIyLVj127oqB6XNLxYmkdG.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0_2_666x500.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"loWMzsIyLVj127oqB6XNLxYmkdG\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0_2_666x500.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0_2_999x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage.jpg\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1024×768 375 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne characteristic of doing it this way is that the life bar stays a constant size, despite the enemy’s distance from the camera. If that is not desired, you could probably do something with the \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/UIComponent.h\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eUIComponent\u003c/a\u003e component, which can be used to render a UI on a static model in the scene. Check the \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/tree/master/Source/Samples/48_Hello3DUI\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e48_Hello3DUI\u003c/a\u003e sample for a demonstration of how to set something like that up. You would likely need to include code, perhaps in a custom component attached to the same node, that would re-orient the static model to mimic billboarding behavior. This custom component could listen for Update, calculate the direction to the camera, and adjust the node’s rotation. Be sure to disable shadows on that model so the lifebar wont cast a shadow.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-10-02T14:04:40.029Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":6,"reads":41,"readers_count":40,"score":68.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5639,"topic_slug":"the-right-way-create-billboard-for-hp-bar-and-problem-with-rendering-how-to","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/JTippetts/DungeonBot3000","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - JTippetts/DungeonBot3000: Dungeon crawler game for gamedev.net challenge","clicks":9},{"url":"https://github.com/JTippetts/DungeonBot3000/blob/master/src/Components/enemylifebar.cpp","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"DungeonBot3000/enemylifebar.cpp at master · JTippetts/DungeonBot3000 · GitHub","clicks":3},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/blob/master/Source/Urho3D/UI/UIComponent.h","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/UIComponent.h at master · urho3d/Urho3D · GitHub","clicks":2},{"url":"https://github.com/urho3d/Urho3D/tree/master/Source/Samples/48_Hello3DUI","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Urho3D/Source/Samples/48_Hello3DUI at master · urho3d/Urho3D · GitHub","clicks":1},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"95ff9bf8b83c45732e739dec610145b6288b8ad0.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":30,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34093,"name":"","username":"Elendil","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/e/df788c/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-10-02T14:49:23.604Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThanks all for answers.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/u/JTippetts\"\u003eJTippetts\u003c/a\u003e good idea, Hello3DUI sample helped me what I did wrong with material, now it is displaying correctly, when bullet hit cube and two or more HP bars are displayed.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am going to try create UI element inside 3D space.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-10-02T14:49:23.604Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":8.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":5639,"topic_slug":"the-right-way-create-billboard-for-hp-bar-and-problem-with-rendering-how-to","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34104,"name":"","username":"Elendil","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/e/df788c/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-10-02T22:08:34.027Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI am creating UI element on box but without success. It display texture on UI instead on box. Box are black or transparent (invisible).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eNode * bb = m_node-\u0026gt;CreateChild(\"HealthBox\");\nbb-\u0026gt;SetScale(Vector3(1.2f, 0.6f, 1.2f));\nbb-\u0026gt;SetPosition(Vector3(0.0f, 1.2f, 0.0f));\nStaticModel * sbb = bb-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;StaticModel\u0026gt;();\nsbb-\u0026gt;SetModel(cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Model\u0026gt;(\"Models/Box.mdl\"));\n\nm_comp = bb-\u0026gt;CreateComponent\u0026lt;UIComponent\u0026gt;();\nm_comp-\u0026gt;GetMaterial()-\u0026gt;SetTechnique(0, cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Technique\u0026gt;(\"Techniques/DiffUnlitParticleAlpha.xml\"));\n\nm_uie = m_comp-\u0026gt;GetRoot();\nm_uie-\u0026gt;SetSize(100, 50);\n\nm_sprite = m_uie-\u0026gt;CreateChild\u0026lt;Sprite\u0026gt;(); //e-\u0026gt;CreateChild\u0026lt;Sprite\u0026gt;();\nm_sprite-\u0026gt;SetTexture(m_texture);\nm_sprite-\u0026gt;SetSize(m_i_width, m_i_height);\nm_sprite-\u0026gt;SetBlendMode(Urho3D::BlendMode::BLEND_ALPHA);\nm_uie-\u0026gt;SetEnabled(true);\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-10-02T22:08:34.027Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":37,"readers_count":36,"score":12.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":5639,"topic_slug":"the-right-way-create-billboard-for-hp-bar-and-problem-with-rendering-how-to","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":34123,"name":"SirNate0","username":"SirNate0","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/9f8e36/{size}.png","created_at":"2019-10-03T14:59:06.622Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNo idea if this is it or not, but what happens if you remove this line?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003em_comp-\u0026gt;GetMaterial()-\u0026gt;SetTechnique(0, cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Technique\u0026gt;(\"Techniques/DiffUnlitParticleAlpha.xml\"))\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre